And a certain man was there, who had been
withered.
thirty and eight years in his infirmity. When Jesus saw
him lying, and knew that he had been now a long time in
‘that case, he saith unto him, Wouldest thou be made whole?
‘The sick man answered him, Sir, I have no man, when the
water is troubled, to put me into the pool: but while I am
coming, another steppeth down before me. Jesus saith unto
him, Arise, take up thy bed, and walk. And straightway
the man was made whole, and took up his bed and walked.
Now it was the sabbath on that day. So the Jews said
unto him that was cured, It is the sabbath, and it is not
lawful for thee to take up thy bed.
