been profited by me is Corban, that is to say, Given to God;
ye no longer suffer him to do aught for his father or his
mother; making void the word of God by your tradition,
which ye have delivered: and many such like things ye do.
And he called to him the multitude again, and said unto
them, Hear me all of you, and understand: there is nothing
from without the man, that going into him can defile him;
but the things which proceed out of the man are those that
And when he was entered into the house
