Now a certain man was sick, Lazarus of Bethany, of the
village of Mary and her sister Martha. And it was that
Mary who anointed the Lord with ointment, and wiped his
feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick. The
sisters therefore sent unto him, saying, Lord, behold, he whom
thou lovest is sick. But when Jesus heard it, he said, This
sickness it not unto death, but for the glory of God, that the
son of God may be glorified thereby.
Now Jesus loved
Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus.
When therefore he
heard that he was sick, he abode at that time two days in
the place where he was. Then after this he saith to the
disciples, Let us go into Judza again. The disciples say
