~ clothes, and saith, What further need have we of witnesses?
Ye have heard the blasphemy: what think ye? And they
all condemned him to be worthy of death. And some began
to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him,
and to say unto him,’ Prophesy: and the officers received
him with blows of their hands.
Now Peter was sitting without in the court: and a maid
came unto him, saying, Thou also wast with Jesus the Gali-
lean. But he denied before them all, saying, I know not
what thou sayest. And when he was gone out into the porch,
another maid saw him, and saith unto them that were there,
This man also was with Jesus of Nazareth. And again he
denied with an oath, I know not the man.
And after a little
while they that stood by came and said to Peter, Of a truth
thou also art one of them; for thy speech maketh thee known.
Then began he to curse and to swear, I know not the man.
And straightway the cock crew. And Peter remembered theTHE
