Pilate saw that he prevailed nothing, but rather that a
tumult was arising, he took water, and washed his. hands
before the multitude, saying, I am innocent of the blood
of this righteous man; see ye to it. And all the people an-
swered and said, His blood be on us, and on our children.
Then released he unto them Barabbas; but Jesus he scourged
and delivered to be crucified.
Then Pilate therefore took Jesus, and scourged him. And
the soldiers platted a crown of thorns, and put it on his
head, and arrayed him in a purple garment; and they came
unto him, and said, Hail, King of the Jews! and they
struck him with their hands.
