After these things Jesus manifested himself again to the
disciples at the sea of Tiberias; and he manifested him-
self on this wise. "There were together Simon Peter, and
Thomas called Didymus, and Nathanael of Cana in Galilee,
and the sons of Zebedee, and two other of his disciples.
Simon Peter saith unto them, I go a fishing. “They say unto
him, We also come with thee. They went forth, and en-
tered into the boat; and that night they took nothing. But
when day was now breaking, Jesus stood on the beach: yet
the disciples knew not that it was Jesus. Jesus therefore
saith unto them, Children, have ye aught to eat? “They an-
swered him, No. And he said unto them, Cast the net on
the right side of the boat, and ye shall find. They cast
therefore, and now they were not able to draw it for the
multitude
of fishes.
