So when Simon Peter
heard that it was the Lord, he girt his coat about him (for
he was naked), and cast himself into the sea. But the other
disciples came in the little boat (for they were not far from
the land, but about two hundred cubits off), dragging the
net full of fishes. So when they got out upon the land, they
see a fire of coals there, and fish laid thereon, and bread.
Jesus saith unto them, Bring of the fish which ye have now
taken. Simon Peter therefore went up, and drew the net to
land, full of great fishes, a hundred and fifty and three: and
for all there were so many, the net was not rent. Jesus saith
unto them, Come and break your fast. And none of theTHE
