which he did. For from many of those that had unclean
spirits, they came out, crying with a loud voice: and many
that were palsied, and that were lame, were healed. And
there was much joy in that city.
But there was a certain man, Simon by name, who be-
foretime in the city used sorcery, and amazed the people of
Samaria, giving out that himself was some great one: to
whom they all gave heed, from the least to the greatest,
saying, This man is that power of God which is called Great.
