them up into his house, and set food before them, and re-
joiced greatly, with all his house, having believed in God.
But when it was day, the magistrates sent the serjeants,
saying, Let those men go. And the jailor reported the words
to Paul, saying, The magistrates have sent to let you go:
now therefore come forth, and go in peace.
But Paul said
unto them, They have beaten us publicly, uncondemned,
men that are Romans, and have cast us into prison; and
do they now cast us out privily? nay verily; but let themTHE
