Owe no man anything, save to love one another: for he
that loveth his neighbor hath fulfilled the law. For this,
Thou shalt not commit adultery, Thou shalt not kill, Thou
shalt not steal, Thou shalt not covet, and if there be any
other commandment, it is summed up in this word, namely,
Thou shalt love thy neighbor as thyself. Love worketh no
ill to his neighbor: love therefore is the fulfilment of the law.
And this, knowing the season, that already it is time for
you to awake out of sleep: for now is salvation nearer to us554
