THE
NEW
TESTAMENT
that they may have the right to come to the tree of life, and
may enter in by the gates into the city. Without are the
dogs, and the sorcerers, and the fornicators, and the murder-
ers, and the idolaters, and every one that loveth and maketh
a lie.
I Jesus have sent mine angel to testify unto you these
things for the churches. I am the root and the offspring of
David, the bright, the morning star.
And the Spirit and the bride say, Come.
And he that
heareth, let him say, Come. And he that is athirst, let him
come: he that will, let him take the water of life freely.
